üçÇ The Taoist Horse Story A farmer&rsquo;s horse runs away.
The neighbours say, &ldquo;Bredda, dat wicked, a wah kinda crosses dat?&rdquo;
The farmer says, &ldquo;We&rsquo;ll see.&rdquo;
The next day the horse comes back with four wild horses.
The neighbours say, &ldquo;Yow boss, blessings a rain pon yuh! Yuh lucky bad man!&rdquo;
The farmer says, &ldquo;We&rsquo;ll see.&rdquo;
The farmer&rsquo;s son tries to ride one of the wild horses and breaks his leg.
